            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "#38272 avoids the crash but I wonder if `add_to_showcmd()` should just return early when the key wasn't typed. I don't think Nvim will ever get to display the showcmd buffer in that case.\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/normal.c b/src/nvim/normal.c\nindex 9f10876a11..168800fc5f 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/normal.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/normal.c\n@@ -1973,7 +1973,7 @@ bool add_to_showcmd(int c)\n     0\n   };\n\n-  if (!p_sc || msg_silent != 0) {\n+  if (!p_sc || msg_silent != 0 || !KeyTyped) {\n     return false;\n   }\n\n```\n\nEDIT: `KeyTyped` is too restrictive, maybe `ex_normal_busy`.",
